{
  "texts": [
    "For instance, Meta's internal test generation system [8] employs a multi-stage filtering pipeline.",
    "It progressively discards tests that fail to compile, fail upon first execution, exhibit flaky (nondeterministic) behavior, or fail to increase code coverage.",
    "This tiered approach ensures that the final test suite is not only executable and reliable but also provides verifiable improvements.",
    "Test Enhancement.The mere fact that a test compiles successfully does not guarantee its effectiveness in detecting defects.",
    "To address the test oracle problem and enhance both the functional effectiveness and non-functional quality of tests, researchers leverage a range of established software engineering techniques.To enhance the fault detection capability of tests, researchers combine LLMs with classic test enhancement techniques."
  ]
}